cscie97.asn4.ecommerce.product

Class Country

  • java.lang.Object
    • cscie97.asn4.ecommerce.product.Country

  • public class Country
extends java.lang.Object
    Content in the Mobile Application Store may be downloaded to consumers devices all over the world. Some countries may not allow certain types of encyption, applications, etc. based on local, regional, or national laws. This class represents a Country and denotes the export status of that country. Countries that have a CLOSED export status disallow application downloads. Note that the IProductAPI will only contain one instance of each unique Country to conserve resources (following the Flyweight pattern).
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    David Killeffer <rayden7@gmail.com>
    See Also:
    ProductAPI, Content, Device

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object compare)
        Since Country objects may be added to collections, and also since the IProductAPI enforces that all country items be unique, this method provides a way to determine if another Country item is the same as the current one. Uses the Apache Commons EqualsBuilder to determine if the two objects are indeed equal to each other.

      • hashCode

        public int hashCode()
        Since Country objects may be added to collections, and also since the IProductAPI enforces that all country items be unique, this method provides a way to get the unique hash code for the current country item. Uses the Apache Commons HashCodeBuilder to generate a unique hash code for the current item based on two randomly chosen unique prime numbers and all the object properties.
